The user updates his self-description as follows: I now favor artful New Wave/post‑punk aesthetics: synth‑driven atmospheres, angular/chorused guitar textures, inventive delays/reverb, and spacious mixes that build mood and rhythmic tension rather than rely on arena bombast. I appreciate production that uses effects creatively to add depth and character, with vocals that sit as part of the texture rather than dominating everything. From my past tastes I still value well‑produced recordings with clear midrange, instrumental separation, dynamic—not flattened—mastering, and thoughtful sequencing that balances up‑tempo tracks and introspective moments. I enjoy recordings that reveal new details on repeat listens and preserve tonal nuance. I dislike formulaic AOR/arena production: predictable big‑chorus bombast, homogenizing loudness/compression, and mixes that bury texture under dense, muddy layering or turn everything into a one‑dimensional stadium sound.

The positive CD has the following updated information: New Wave/post‑punk set: synth‑driven atmospheres, angular chorused guitars and inventive delays/reverb; spacious mixes place vocals as texture with clear midrange, dynamic mastering and thoughtful sequencing that balances kinetic tracks and introspection—reveals new details on repeat listens, appealing to listeners who value texture and nuance over stadium bombast.

